But the richness of a silver Vein is thus discerned;


If in 100 l. weight of the Ore, there be above 3 l. weight, it is rich, 'otherwise it is poor, as is that which consists of unwrought silver. Whether the colour be leaden, red, white, black, ash-coloured, purple, yellow, liver-coloured, or of any other sort; such also sometimes is the Vein of flint, slate, and marble, if much do adhere unto them. Sometimes in Fire-stones, Cadmia, Ore of Brass, Lead Ore, and Ore of Antimony.

